data.text: Day four of the search continues. A Coast Guard spokesperson says that weather could’ve definitely been a factor in the 49ft Cary Marine sinking, as well as their ship malfunctioning. Estimated to have sunk around 7:30 PM on Saturday. Tropical storm Nestor made landfall that day

entity.name: Disturbance in Gulf of Mexico officially becomes Tropical Storm Nestor, NHC says
entity.description: The National Hurricane Center confirmed that the developing system in the Gulf of Mexico is now Tropical Storm Nestor. In the report, the NHC warns that "dangerous storm surge and tropical storm force winds [are] expected along portions of the northern Gulf Coast" on Friday.

data.text: Soaking wet awaiting the storm. Live coverage with @abc27 #StormNestor https://t.co/gQhgTEcGQz

Storm surge beginning to recede from #Wakulla coast

Dave was supposed to go on the road at 4. When I got home he said that was moved up to midnight. County is thinking coastal weather is going to get rough by 2 am. If you are doing storm prayers, include Dave please. I'm always a worried LEO wife.  #wakulla #TropicalStormNestor
